Leveraged positions are opened in the following steps: 1. Supplying collateral from the user to Aave 2. Taking Aave flash loan and supplying additional collateral 3. borrowDebtToken(uint256).details: Borrows debt token and sends it to the owner

params._amount: The amount of debt token to borrow

burnPosition(address).details: Can only be called by the owner (NFT holder) and only if the position is safe to close      Position must be fully unwound (no debt) before burning

params._params: struct containing:        - desiredLeverage: The desired leverage multiplier with 4 decimals (e.g., 30000 = 3x)        - collateralAmount: The amount of collateral the user will provide (in collateral token units)        - collateralTokenPrice: Price of collateral token in USD with 8 decimals        - borrowTokenPrice: Price of borrow token in USD with 8 decimals

returns.borrowAmount: The amount to borrow from Aave (in borrow token units)
returns.flashLoanAmount: The amount to flash loan (in collateral token units)

calculateUnwindParams(uint256).details: if the _debtTeRepay is equal to or more than the actual debt, the position will be fully closed

params._debtToRepay: the amount of debt to repay on the position reducing the position size

returns.collateralToWithdraw: The amount of collateral to withdraw from Aave (includes slippage buffer)
returns.debtAmount: The total debt amount to repay

createLeveragedPosition(uint256,uint256,.details: Process:      1. User transfers collateral to contract      2. Flash loan additional collateral      3. Pay Stratax fee      4. Supply total collateral (user + flash loan) to Aave      5. Borrow debt tokens from Aave      6. Swap debt tokens to collateral via 1inch      7. Repay flash loan with swap proceeds      8. Supply any leftover collateral to Aave

params._borrowAmount: Amount to borrow from Aave (from calculateOpenParams)
params._minReturnAmount: Minimum collateral expected from swap for slippage protection
params._oneInchSwapData: Encoded calldata from 1inch API for debt  collateral swap

executeOperation(address,uint256,uint256.details: This function must be implemented to handle flash loans from Aave V3      It routes to either _executeOpenOperation or _executeUnwindOperation based on OperationType

params._initiator: The address that initiated the flash loan (must be this contract)
params._params: Encoded parameters containing OperationType and operation-specific params

returns._0: bool Returns true if operation succeeds, reverts otherwise
The address of the borrow token
The address of the collateral token

getCurrentLeverage().details: Leverage = Total Collateral Value / Equity      Where Equity = Total Collateral Value - Total Debt Value      Uses StrataxOracle for price feeds (8 decimals)

returns.currentLeverage: The current leverage with 4 decimals (e.g., 30000 = 3x)         Returns 0 if there is no position (no collateral)

getFreeCollateral().details: Free collateral is collateral not currently backing any debt

returns._0: The amount of free collateral in collateral token units

params._borrowTokenPrice: Price of borrow token in USD with 8 decimals
params._collateralTokenPrice: Price of collateral token in USD with 8 decimals

returns._0: The amount of free collateral in collateral token units

getMaxAchievableLeverageBinary().details: uses binary search and should call this off chain to save gas

returns.maxLeverage: The actual leverage that can be achieved after fees

getPositionUsdValue().details: Uses StrataxOracle for price feeds (8 decimals)

returns.positionValueUsd: The current position value in USD with 8 decimals         Returns 0 if position is underwater (debt value >= collateral value)

initialize((address,address,address,addr.details: Can only be called once due to initializer modifier

isLeverageSafe(uint256,uint256,uint256).details: considers stratax fee and flashloan fee when verifying leverage

params._strataxFee: Strtax fee as a percent with 4 decimals of precision

returns._0: isSafe bool whether the supplied leverage is achievable
The address of the owner (NFT holder)

repayDebtToken(uint256).details: Transfers debt token from user and repays to Aave

params._amount: The amount of debt token to repay (use type(uint256).max to repay all)

supplyCollateral(uint256).details: Transfers collateral from user and supplies it to Aave

params._amount: The amount of collateral to supply

unwindPosition(uint256,uint256,bytes,uin.details: Process:      1. Flash loan the debt token amount      2. Repay all Aave debt      3. Withdraw collateral from Aave      4. Swap collateral back to debt token via 1inch      5. Pay Stratax fee      6. Repay flash loan + premium      7. Any leftover is supplied back to Aave or sent to user

params._collateralToWithdraw: Amount of collateral to withdraw from Aave (should include buffer for fees/slippage)
params._debtAmount: Total amount of debt to repay (from calculateUnwindParams)
params._minReturnAmount: Minimum debt tokens expected from swap for slippage protection
params._oneInchSwapData: Encoded calldata from 1inch API for collateral  debt token swap

update1InchRouter(address).details: Allows owner to update the 1inch router in case of upgrades or changes in the 1inch protocol

params._newRouter: The address of the new 1inch router

updateFlashLoanFee().details: Fetches the current flash loan premium from Aave and updates the cached value      Can only be called by the position owner

updateMaxLeverageOffset(uint256).details: Allows owner to adjust the max leverage offset to be more or less conservative based on market conditions.      The offset is used to reduce the effective LTV when calculating max leverage,      providing a safety buffer to prevent positions from being too close to the liquidation threshold.      The offset is expressed with 4 decimal precision (e.g., 75 = 0.75%).

params._newOffset: The new max leverage offset (must be <= 500, i.e., 5%)

withdrawCollateral(uint256).details: Withdraws collateral and sends it to the owner

params._amount: The amount of collateral to withdraw (use type(uint256).max to withdraw all)
